    {
        "content": "<p>Here's the breaking changes entry in the release notes:</p>\n<blockquote>\n<p>The <code>Parsec</code> library has moved from <code>Lean.Data.Parsec</code> to <code>Std.Internal.Parsec</code>. The <code>Parsec</code> type is now more general with a parameter for an iterable. Users parsing strings can migrate to <code>Parser</code> in the <code>Std.Internal.Parsec.String</code> namespace, which also includes string-focused parsing combinators. (<a href=\"https://github.com/leanprover/lean4/pull/4774\">#4774</a>)</p>\n</blockquote>\n<p>You should be able to use <code>Parser</code> instead of <code>Parsec</code>.</p>",
